# i18n and l10n Standards

- Wrap user-facing strings with translation functions (`__`, `_e`, `esc_html__`, `esc_attr__`).
- Always use the correct project text domain consistently across theme/plugin files.
- Use placeholders instead of string concatenation in translated strings.
- Add translator comments for ambiguous placeholders and context-sensitive strings.
- Escape translated output by context (`esc_html__`, `esc_attr__`, `wp_kses_post` as needed).
- Do not hardcode date/time/currency formats; use WordPress locale-aware APIs.
- Keep JS/UI labels translation-ready through localized script data or translation APIs.
- When adding new strings, ensure language files are updated in the release process.
